        description:
            "What You´ll Do:\r\n\r\nThe Global Automation team develops and runs a wide range of first-class solutions that empower Criteo´s commercial and operations teams to maximise their business impact. \r\n\r\nWe build scalable, reliable, and interoperable systems, that constantly need to adapt to business priorities and evolutions. And we build the applications, APIs and UIs to supply first-class service to our users. \r\n\r\nOur team empower internal teams by crafting solutions, APIs, ETL pipelines and frameworks that are meant to provide commercial stakeholders with secure and fast access to Criteo data and the related insights necessary to manage their portfolios effectively. \r\n\r\nYou will be leading a team of engineers in a multicultural and diverse environment alongside highly motivated colleagues and a talented team of highly skilled engineers on products that make a real business impact. \r\n\r\nAs a Team Lead, you will lead a cross-functional agile team of engineers responsible for developing some of our most critical solutions in Global Automation. \r\n\r\nYou will be an agile coach for the team, driving all aspects of software development, helping with blockers, identifying risks, and updating progress to leadership. \r\n\r\nYou will be a champion of technical excellence, a key mentor to your development team and a strong contributor in driving development best practices and standards splitting your time between line management duties and software development. \r\n\r\nBalancing both line management responsibilities and hands-on software development, you embody a servant leadership approach. Your success lies in your ability to coach and mentor effectively, ensuring the continuous growth and contribution of each team member. By fostering an environment of ongoing improvement, you empower the team to confidently own their technical solutions from inception to production. \r\n\r\nKey responsibilities \r\n\r\n- Lead and manage a group of engineers\r\n- Implement and champion agile practices\r\n\r\n- Actively participate in hiring.\r\n- Support and mentor engineers through regular 1:1s.\r\n- Foster the career growth of direct reports\r\n- Collaborate with leadership, product managers, UX designers, and internal stakeholders.\r\n- Provide architectural oversight and technical leadership.\r\n- Write reusable, testable, secure, and efficient code in Python.\r\n\r\nWho You Are:\r\n\r\n- Have Bachelor´s/Master´s degree in Software Engineering or related field.\r\n- Have a passion in leading and managing Agile teams.\r\n- Maintain an enthusiasm for software development, best practices, and clean code.\r\n- Strong experience delivering scalable quality software products in Python.\r\n- Critical thinker with problem-solving skills.\r\n- Ability to interact with both technical and non-technical audiences.\r\n\r\nBonus \r\n\r\n- Good understanding of security best practices.\r\n- Having some hands-on experience with data science or machine learning.\r\n- Knowledge in alerting stacks such as Prometheus or others.\r\n- Experience with ETL pipelines.\r\n\r\n- Experience programming in other languages (PHP, Ruby or C#).\r\n\r\nWe acknowledge that many candidates may not meet every single role requirement listed above. If your experience looks a little different from our requirements but you believe that you can still bring value to the role, we´d love to see your application!\r\n\r\n\r\nWhy Join Us:\r\n\r\nAt Criteo, we take pride in being a caring culture and are committed to providing our employees with valuable benefits that support their physical, emotional and financial wellbeing, their interests and the important life events. We aim to create a place where people can grow and learn from each other while having a meaningful impact. We want to set you up for success in your job, and an important part of that includes comprehensive perks & benefits. Benefits may vary depending on the country where you work and the nature of your employment with Criteo. When determining compensation, we carefully consider a wide range of job-related factors, including experience, knowledge, skills, education, and location. These factors can cause your compensation to vary.",
